The paper deals with the fundamental limits of joint decoding of signals from multiple users in a multi-antenna base station, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves communication networks (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI) techniques. The use of constellations and scaling behavior suggests that it could also be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with the performance of decoders, which could fall under computer communications (cs.COM).
